Ultimately it's incredibly carceral, does not open pathways for communication and reconciliation, and it makes everyone feel gross and bad.

The loudest person was almost never the victim (who usually wanted to not be involved/rehash their trauma), and there was never room to talk about healing or growth for anyone involved--not the harmed or the harmer. There was also no chance for acknowledgement of growth.

As someone who has closely witnessed call outs in multiple art communities, I feel like I can gesture around me and say it mostly hurt people already on the margins, gave platforms to people who wielded their power irresponsibly, and did not actually fix any community problems.
